{
    "name":  "02 - Human Approval Gate (Shared Subworkflow)",
    "nodes":  [
                  {
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "content":  "## ðŸ›‘ Human Approval Gate\n\n**Purpose:** Pauses a workflow and sends an approval request via email (or Slack). Resumes only after a human clicks Approve or Reject.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Create an SMTP credential named `SMTP Email`\n2. Set `NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_TO` environment variable\n3. Ensure the n8n webhook URL is accessible from the approver\u0027s email client\n\n**Input:**\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Approve: Weekly Feedback Report\",\n  \"summary\": \"3 critical insights, 12 feature requests...\",\n  \"details\": {},\n  \"approver_email\": \"pm@yourcompany.com\",\n  \"timeout_hours\": 24\n}\n```\n\n**Output:**\n```json\n{\n  \"decision\": \"approved\",\n  \"decided_at\": \"2025-01-01T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"comment\": \"\"\n}\n```\n\nâš ï¸ The workflow pauses here until the approver responds or the timeout expires.",
                                         "height":  420,
                                         "width":  520,
                                         "color":  3
                                     },
                      "id":  "sticky-approval-setup",
                      "name":  "Setup Instructions",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
                      "typeVersion":  1,
                      "position":  [
                                       0,
                                       -240
                                   ]
                  },
                  {
                      "parameters":  {

                                     },
                      "id":  "trigger-approval",
                      "name":  "When Called by Another Workflow",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.executeWorkflowTrigger",
                      "typeVersion":  1,
                      "position":  [
                                       240,
                                       100
                                   ]
                  },
                  {
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "jsCode":  "// Prepare approval request metadata\nconst input = $input.first().json;\n\nconst approvalId = `approval_${Date.now()}_${Math.random().toString(36).substring(2, 9)}`;\nconst approverEmail = input.approver_email || process.env.NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_TO || \u0027team@example.com\u0027;\nconst timeoutHours = input.timeout_hours || 24;\nconst expiresAt = new Date(Date.now() + timeoutHours * 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString();\n\n// Build approval and rejection URLs (using n8n\u0027s resume URL pattern)\n// In production these are generated by the Wait node â€” this is for the email template\nconst webhookBase = process.env.WEBHOOK_URL || \u0027http://localhost:5678\u0027;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...input,\n    approvalId,\n    approverEmail,\n    timeoutHours,\n    expiresAt,\n    webhookBase,\n    createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n  }\n}];"
                                     },
                      "id":  "prepare-approval",
                      "name":  "Prepare Approval Request",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.code",
                      "typeVersion":  2,
                      "position":  [
                                       460,
                                       100
                                   ]
                  },
                  {
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "sendTo":  "={{ $json.approverEmail }}",
                                         "subject":  "Action required: {{ $json.title }}",
                                         "message":  "\u003chtml\u003e\u003cbody style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch2 style=\"color: #333;\"\u003e{{ $json.title }}\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #555;\"\u003e{{ $json.summary }}\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 20px 0;\"\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eDetails:\u003c/strong\u003e\n\u003cpre style=\"overflow-x: auto; white-space: pre-wrap;\"\u003e{{ JSON.stringify($json.details, null, 2) }}\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp style=\"color: #888; font-size: 13px;\"\u003eThis request expires at: {{ $json.expiresAt }}\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"margin: 30px 0;\"\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"{{ $execution.resumeUrl }}?approve=true\" style=\"background: #22c55e; color: white; padding: 12px 24px; border-radius: 6px; text-decoration: none; margin-right: 12px; font-size: 16px;\"\u003eâœ… Approve\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003ca href=\"{{ $execution.resumeUrl }}?approve=false\" style=\"background: #ef4444; color: white; padding: 12px 24px; border-radius: 6px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 16px;\"\u003eâŒ Reject\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp style=\"color: #aaa; font-size: 12px;\"\u003eSent by n8n Product \u0026 Founder Automation OS\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/body\u003e\u003c/html\u003e",
                                         "options":  {
                                                         "allowUnauthorizedCerts":  false
                                                     }
                                     },
                      "id":  "send-approval-email",
                      "name":  "Send Approval Email",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.emailSend",
                      "typeVersion":  2.1,
                      "position":  [
                                       680,
                                       100
                                   ],
                      "credentials":  {
                                          "smtp":  {
                                                       "id":  "SMTP_CREDENTIAL_ID",
                                                       "name":  "SMTP Email"
                                                   }
                                      },
                      "retryOnFail":  true,
                      "maxTries":  3,
                      "waitBetweenTries":  1000
                  },
                  {
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "resume":  "webhook",
                                         "options":  {
                                                         "webhookSuffix":  "={{ $json.approvalId }}",
                                                         "limitWaitTime":  true,
                                                         "limitType":  "afterTimeInterval",
                                                         "resumeAmount":  "={{ $(\u0027Prepare Approval Request\u0027).first().json.timeoutHours }}",
                                                         "resumeUnit":  "hours"
                                                     }
                                     },
                      "id":  "wait-for-approval",
                      "name":  "Wait for Approval (or Timeout)",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.wait",
                      "typeVersion":  1.1,
                      "position":  [
                                       900,
                                       100
                                   ],
                      "webhookId":  "approval-gate-webhook"
                  },
                  {
                      "parameters":  {
                                         "jsCode":  "// Process the approval response\nconst waitResponse = $input.first().json;\nconst originalRequest = $(\u0027Prepare Approval Request\u0027).first().json;\n\n// Check if this was a timeout (no query params) or a webhook response\nconst isTimeout = !waitResponse?.query?.approve \u0026\u0026 !waitResponse?.body?.approve;\nconst isApproved = String(waitResponse?.query?.approve || waitResponse?.body?.approve).toLowerCase() === \u0027true\u0027;\n\nconst decision = isTimeout ? \u0027timeout\u0027 : (isApproved ? \u0027approved\u0027 : \u0027rejected\u0027);\nconst comment = waitResponse?.query?.comment || waitResponse?.body?.comment || \u0027\u0027;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    approvalId: originalRequest.approvalId,\n    title: originalRequest.title,\n    decision,\n    decided_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n    comment,\n    approved: decision === \u0027approved\u0027,\n    timeout: decision === \u0027timeout\u0027,\n  }\n}];"
                                     },
                      "id":  "process-decision",
                      "name":  "Process Approval Decision",
                      "type":  "n8n-nodes-base.code",
                      "typeVersion":  2,
                      "position":  [
                                       1120,
                                       100
                                   ]
                  }
              ],
    "connections":  {
